"Mostly clear yellow-amber pour with a fluffy two finger pure white head with great retention and lacing.  Wonderful perfumey, flowery, citrus nose with hints of tangerine, grapefruit, floral hops, pine, caramel, and brown sugar.  The taste mirrors the nose with tons of floral, perfumey hoppiness along with hints of grapefruit, tangerine, orange peel, pine, caramel, lemon zest, grass, and brown sugar.  The mouthfeel is medium bodied with fizzy carbonation, incredible balance, and a great tangy-sweet finish.  Overall, this is a hugely drinkable beer that's full of flavor that I could definitely drink on a regular basis."
